{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ef3c40be-f4a3-4abc-98af-195a884a4b1f","content":"The HotReload extension is already referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet test` and the `--hotreload` flag:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in **watch mode**. It will:\n\n1. Run your tests initially\n2. **Wait** for you to edit and save source files\n3. **Re-run** affected tests automatically on each save — without a full rebuild\n\nThis is much faster than repeatedly running `dotnet test` because it applies changes in-place via hot reload rather than doing a cold build each time.\n\n**Tips:**\n- Just edit `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (or the code under test) in your editor, save, and tests re-run instantly.\n- Press `Ctrl+C` to exit the hot reload session.\n- You can combine it with a filter, e.g. `dotnet test --hotreload --filter \"MethodName\"` to focus on specific failing tests.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2eb9c334-0c32-45a2-a8de-0d7e44463e4a","outputTokens":221},"id":"af2545dd-847f-4325-bc17-b349793d5df2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:49.280Z","parentId":"04e4059e-8009-4433-acdb-100008de5bee"}
